ared by Wayde van Niekerk (@waydedreamer) Meanwhile,Noah Lylesanchored the US 4x100m men toWorld Athletics Relaysglory, andGabby Thomasbagged a quickfire double as the American team won four of the five golds on offer in Nassau on Sunday.\", \"from\": 1315, \"to\": 1563, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1332, \"end\": 1349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wayde_van_Niekerk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wayde van Niekerk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wayde_van_Niekerk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wayde_van_Niekerk\"}, {\"begin\": 1493, \"end\": 1501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999999217835, \"rank\": 7.538244139261347e-11, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1546, \"end\": 1552, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duchy_of_Nassau\", \"score\": 0.9992571150401252, \"rank\": 0.0007401816496152822, \"text\": \"Nassau\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duchy_of_Nassau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duchy_of_Nassau\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A post\", \"from\": 1315, \"to\": 1321}, {\"ngram\": \"@waydedreamer\", \"from\": 1351, \"to\": 1364}, {\"ngram\": \"Noah\", \"from\": 1376, \"to\": 1380}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 1409, \"to\": 1412}, {\"ngram\": \"andGabby\", \"from\": 1444, \"to\": 1452}, {\"ngram\": \"a quickfire\", \"from\": 1466, \"to\": 1477}, {\"ngram\": \"the five golds\", \"from\": 1518, \"to\": 1532}, {\"ngram\": \"offer\", \"from\": 1536, \"to\": 1541}, {\"ngram\": \"Sunday\", \"from\": 1555, \"to\": 1561}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles took the baton from Kyree King and accelerated through the line in 37.40 seconds after slick early handovers by Courtney Lindsey and Kenneth Bednarek.\", \"from\": 156